## Version 2 (v6.2)

### Prompt
You are a sales specialist at Flexikitch. Write a follow-up email to a café owner who hasn’t responded in 5 days. Include value reminder, social proof, and CTA. Keep polite, non-pushy, under 150 words.

Respond 
Hi [Name],

I just wanted to follow up on my previous message—completely understand how busy things can get.

At Flexikitch, we’ve helped café owners gain better visibility over their costs and streamline operations, leading to improved margins without adding extra workload. Several hospitality businesses we’ve worked with have seen noticeable improvements in profitability within a short time.

If this is something you’d like to explore, I’d be happy to share a few quick insights tailored to your café.
Would you be open to a brief 10-minute chat this week?

Best regards,
[Your Name]
Flexikitch


### Change Made
Included timing (no response)
Added basic structure

### Observed Effect
More relevant emails
Still lacked persuasive elements

### Lesson Learned
Need social proof and CTA
